<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="154" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d154">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 857.857/81</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Havre</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Osborne</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Havre</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-23">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 23, 1917</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received midnight.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Norwegian steamer <hi rend="italic">Alice</hi>, unarmed, no
                                passengers, carrying coal Port Albert to Tréport, cannonaded without
                                warning by enemy submarine, nationality unknown, off Fécamp,
                                February 21. More than 20 shots fired, imperilling crew 14 including
                                    <persName>Theo Joseph</persName>, American negro, born
                                Fernandina, Fla. <hi rend="italic">Alice</hi> then sunk by bombs.
                                Depositions Norwegian captain and <persName>Joseph</persName>
                                taken.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Osborne</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>